fr.ecp.Group52_Project_IS1220_part1_AVEROUS_TOPUZ.Model.Network.Station

Class StationPlus

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.ecp.Group52_Project_IS1220_part1_AVEROUS_TOPUZ.Model.Network.Station.Station

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Observable, VisitableItems

    public class StationPlus
extends Station
    Stations are among the most important elements of the myVelib system. A station is where bicycles can be rented and dropped. It consists of a number of parking slots where bikes are stored and of a terminal which users can interact with in order to rent bicycles. Parking slots can be be occupied by a bicycle, free or out-of-order. A station is located in a specific place specified by GPS coordinates. A station can be on service or offline: if it is offline all of its parking bays as well as the terminal cannot be used. There exist two types of stations, a standard type, and a plus type. This class represents the plus type. When a user who holds a Velib card drops a bicycle at a plus station, they earns 5 minutes credits in their time balance. Each station has a unique numerical ID and so each parking slot (within a station) has a unique numerical ID.
    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    Pierre Averous, Nicolas Topuz
